China will inform Russia at any moment of the latest situation, to enable the latter to make quick and timely responses, the spokesman said.
Zhang, asked at the meeting to respond to the public concern over the water poison accident that occurred in northeast China's Songhua River, vowed to take tougher measures to reduce the emission of pollutants.
China and Russia have both pledged to cooperate closely to handle the pollution of the Songhua River in northeast China's Heilongjiang Province, said Chinese Foreign Ministry spokesman Liu Jianchao here Thursday.
